value.title: Biden pick Neera Tanden repudiated Michelle Obama catchphrase, said 'going high doesn't f--king work'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden's nominee to head the Office and Management and Budget, Neera Tanden, in 2017 repudiated the Michelle Obama catchphrase "when they go low we go high," tweeting that "going high doesn't f**king work."

value.title: Biden says coronavirus relief package during lame-duck period likely 'just a start'
value.excerpt: Lawmakers have just days to reach an agreement on additional relief before Congress closes for the year.

value.title: Mnuchin says Trump 'wants to make sure there is not a shutdown'
value.excerpt: Two of the top negotiators in Washington -- House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin -- spoke Tuesday afternoon about funding the government, weeks after talks broke down for a new stimulus package to respond to the Covid-19 pandemic and its economic fallout.

value.title: Biden pick for OMB director will push globalist policies that cost US jobs: Huckabee
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden’s pick for director of the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) will push globalist policies that will lead to the loss of U.S. jobs, former Arkansas Gov. Mike Huckabee warned Tuesday.

value.title: Cuomo warns that Trump vaccination plans fail minorities, undocumented immigrants
value.excerpt: New York Democratic Gov. Andrew Cuomo penned a letter Tuesday calling for U.S. Health and Human Services Secretary Alex Azar to alter the upcoming vaccination program he says is inadequately serving "Black, Brown, Asian and low-income communities."

value.title: Frontrunners for Kamala Harris Senate seat praised Fidel Castro
value.excerpt: Two frontrunners for Vice President-elect Kamala Harris' Senate seat have praised former Cuban dictator Fidel Castro.

value.title: Live politics updates: Biden on COVID stimulus: 'Help is on the way'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden called on Congress to approve an economic stimulus plan. He also suggested that a package would be followed up.

value.title: Pence returns to Georgia on Friday; Obama stars in new Ossoff TV ad
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence will return to Georgia on Friday to hit the campaign trail in the state’s twin Jan. 5 Senate runoff elections, where the Republicans' Senate majority is at stake.

value.title: Fired cybersecurity chief may include Trump attorney in lawsuit over death threats
value.excerpt: Former Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency Director Chris Krebs said Tuesday he plans to take legal action against people who have threatened his life after he disagreed with his onetime boss, President Trump, over the validity of the Nov. 3 election.

value.title: The Daily 202: Ousted U.S. attorney, removed by Barr as he investigated Trump associates, lands new job
value.excerpt: During a noon meeting in a suite at the Pierre hotel in Manhattan on a Friday in June, Attorney General Bill Barr pressured Geoffrey Berman to step aside as the U.S. attorney for the Southern District of New York.

value.title: Sean Hannity says Trump should pardon himself and his family to avoid a ‘witch hunt.’ Experts say it’s not that simple.
value.excerpt: Five days after President Trump pardoned his former national security adviser Michael Flynn, Fox News host and Trump ally Sean Hannity offered a suggestion on Monday about who the president should pardon next: himself and his family.

value.title: Executive at nonprofit that helped in Georgia audit has history of anti-Trump tweets
value.excerpt: The executive director of a San Francisco-based nonprofit that was tapped by Georgia’s secretary of state to assist in the state’s audit has a history of anti-Trump tweets, but has insisted that he does not “bring them to work.”

value.title: Biden expected to introduce key members of economic team Tuesday
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden and Vice President-elect Kamala Harris on Tuesday afternoon are expected to introduce key members of their economic team at an event in Wilmington, Delaware.

value.title: Some Taiwanese immigrants fear Biden will ‘Make China Great Again.’ Can he win them over?
value.excerpt: Among Southern Californians with roots in Taiwan, there is strong support for President Trump. Some are single-issue voters who value their homeland’s interests above domestic issues.

value.title: Analysis: GOP silence on Trump's false election claims recalls McCarthy era
value.excerpt: The silence of congressional Republican leaders as President Donald Trump's unfounded claims of election fraud grow wilder and more venomous increasingly resembles the party's deference to Sen. Joe McCarthy during the worst excesses of his anti-Communist crusade in the early 1950s.

value.title: Analysis: How Joe Biden and Mark Kelly show Arizona is now a purple state
value.excerpt: Democrat Mark Kelly will be sworn in on Wednesday as Arizona's junior US senator, finishing the final two years of the term won by the late Sen. John McCain in 2016. Both President-elect Joe Biden and Kelly were certified as the winners of their respective Arizona races on Monday.

value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: The Trump campaign is filing a lawsuit to the Wisconsin Supreme Court Tuesday -- alleging abuse around the process of absentee voting in the state, which they say affected approximately 220,000 ballots.

value.excerpt: A Pennsylvania state senator abruptly left a meeting with President Trump after being told he was positive for the coronavirus, a source told AP.

value.title: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris picks Tina Flournoy as her chief of staff
value.excerpt: Tina Flournoy, who is currently serving as chief of staff to former President Bill Clinton, has been chosen to be Vice President-elect Kamala Harris' chief of staff, according to a source with knowledge of the decision.

value.title: Arizona Gov. Doug Ducey defends election process after Trump attack
value.excerpt: Arizona Republican Gov. Doug Ducey sent a lengthy string of tweets Monday night defending the state's election process after being attacked by President Donald Trump for his handling of it.
